00:53:38.060 --> 00:53:42.150
that these guys you know they had
a lot of these guys after the war,

00:53:42.150 --> 00:53:47.190
they knew where a lot of these
guys were but there was no effort

00:53:47.190 --> 00:53:50.600
to really make them accountable
for what they had done.

00:53:50.600 --> 00:53:52.400
Yes, ma'am.

00:53:52.400 --> 00:54:14.520
[ Inaudible ]

00:54:14.520 --> 00:54:16.010
You know what?

00:54:16.010 --> 00:54:20.320
I think the broader question
is why did they bother holding

00:54:20.320 --> 00:54:21.620
onto this stuff?

00:54:21.620 --> 00:54:25.450
Yes. So why did they bother and
that's of course the question

00:54:25.450 --> 00:54:29.130
and I've got a great book I
can suggest to read about that

00:54:29.130 --> 00:54:30.780
which is available in
the back of the room

00:54:30.780 --> 00:54:33.890
by the way, and available on audio.

00:54:33.890 --> 00:54:36.820
But there are a few
answers to that question.

00:54:36.820 --> 00:54:40.900
First, the Nazis were
trying to show themselves

00:54:40.900 --> 00:54:44.560
to be cultured and
enlightened people.

00:54:44.560 --> 00:54:49.960
They were very proud and
Germany had long been a culture

00:54:49.960 --> 00:54:56.360 position:56%
that prided itself on its books,
and so you know this was great poets

00:54:56.360 --> 00:55:00.060
and novelists and writers
had all come from Germany

00:55:00.060 --> 00:55:05.090
and so they were working very
hard to show themselves to be,

00:55:05.090 --> 00:55:10.910
to be an enlightened people, a
scholarly intellectual people.

00:55:10.910 --> 00:55:16.050
This was the intellectual veneer
that was put over the ugliness

00:55:16.050 --> 00:55:18.960
of Nazi Germany, that's
one reason they did it.

00:55:18.960 --> 00:55:22.090 position:56%
The other reason or among the other
reasons, there are a lot of reasons,

00:55:22.090 --> 00:55:24.570
part of it was just triumphalism.

00:55:24.570 --> 00:55:28.010
Look at how we have become victors

00:55:28.010 --> 00:55:30.830
over this vanquished
Jewish civilization.

00:55:30.830 --> 00:55:33.030
I think that's what they
were trying to do as well.

00:55:33.030 --> 00:55:34.330
One of the other phenomena

00:55:34.330 --> 00:55:38.400
in play was what one scholar
called working towards the fuhrer.

00:55:38.400 --> 00:55:41.490
Hitler it turns out
was a very good orator.

00:55:41.490 --> 00:55:43.780
He was not a very good administer.

00:55:43.780 --> 00:55:49.140 position:56%
He would come in late in the day, he
would when his underlings would get

00:55:49.140 --> 00:55:52.100
in fights and conflicts with
one another, he didn't want

00:55:52.100 --> 00:55:53.580
to be bothered with that at all.

00:55:53.580 --> 00:55:56.880
He kind of enjoyed letting
them, watching them fight it

00:55:56.880 --> 00:55:59.180
out amongst themselves and it made

00:55:59.180 --> 00:56:03.670
for a very chaotic administrative
structure within the Nazi regime.

00:56:03.670 --> 00:56:07.770
I touched on that in my talk
and they were all competing,

00:56:07.770 --> 00:56:10.320
they were all trying to
get Hitler's attention,

00:56:10.320 --> 00:56:14.780
and so if your agency could
get more books more material

00:56:14.780 --> 00:56:19.310
than the other Nazi agency,
if Rosenberg's ERR could

00:56:19.310 --> 00:56:25.060
out do the RSHA in their looting
efforts, then that would be a badge

00:56:25.060 --> 00:56:27.030
of pride that they
could wear as they went

00:56:27.030 --> 00:56:28.910
and appeared before the fuhrer.

00:56:28.910 --> 00:56:31.150
So they were trying to
impress Hitler as well.

00:56:31.150 --> 00:56:35.390
So there were a lot of reasons that
they did this and it all culminated

00:56:35.390 --> 00:56:42.400
in this largest campaign in
history of literary pillage.

00:56:42.400 --> 00:56:45.380
So that's a partial
answer to your question.

00:56:45.380 --> 00:56:49.630
I'm not sure I have a full answer
but I hope that's a partial answer.

